WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:15.120
Lucky Number by John Milne

00:15.120 --> 00:19.200
Cafe Colombo is always busy.

00:19.200 --> 00:24.280
There are always people sitting at the tables in Cafe Colombo.

00:24.280 --> 00:28.040
The men and women are all well-dressed.

00:28.040 --> 00:35.520
They drink coffee, they eat ice cream, they read newspapers.

00:35.520 --> 00:39.360
Charlie does not sit in Cafe Colombo.

00:39.360 --> 00:42.680
Charlie is not well-dressed.

00:42.680 --> 00:47.320
He sits on the pavement outside Cafe Colombo.

00:47.320 --> 00:51.320
He sits on a small box.

00:51.320 --> 00:54.080
Charlie is a shoe shine boy.

00:54.080 --> 00:57.040
Charlie shines shoes.

00:57.040 --> 00:59.360
He does not go to school.

00:59.360 --> 01:06.840
He works all day.

01:06.840 --> 01:10.160
Charlie shines men's shoes.

01:10.160 --> 01:13.240
He shines lady's shoes.

01:13.240 --> 01:15.880
He shines black shoes.

01:15.880 --> 01:18.840
He shines brown shoes.

01:18.840 --> 01:22.400
He shines blue shoes.

01:22.400 --> 01:36.200
Shoe shine, shoe shine, ten cents, ten cents, ten cents a shine.

01:36.200 --> 01:41.080
A man in Cafe Colombo shouts, Charlie.

01:41.080 --> 01:44.200
Charlie runs into Cafe Colombo.

01:44.200 --> 01:47.320
He puts his box at the man's feet.

01:47.320 --> 01:51.080
The man puts one foot on the box.

01:51.080 --> 01:54.240
The man's shoes are black.

01:54.240 --> 01:57.880
The man's shoes are dirty.

01:57.880 --> 02:02.120
Charlie cleans the man's shoes.

02:02.120 --> 02:05.640
The man gives Charlie ten cents.

02:05.640 --> 02:08.720
Charlie takes the ten cent coin.

02:08.720 --> 02:11.120
He picks up his box.

02:11.120 --> 02:18.680
He goes back to the pavement.

02:18.680 --> 02:22.680
An old man walks slowly along the pavement.

02:22.680 --> 02:26.880
The old man is carrying a large board.

02:26.880 --> 02:29.800
There is a notice on the board.

02:29.800 --> 02:33.720
The old man is selling lottery tickets.

02:33.720 --> 02:40.680
Buy a ticket, win a fortune, one dollar a ticket.

02:40.680 --> 02:43.880
Give me a ticket, hurry.

02:43.880 --> 02:48.960
A well-dressed man in Cafe Colombo is shouting.

02:48.960 --> 02:52.400
The ticket seller gives the man a ticket.

02:52.400 --> 02:59.080
The man gives the ticket seller a dollar.

02:59.080 --> 03:01.880
The well-dressed man is in a hurry.

03:01.880 --> 03:04.240
A taxi is waiting.

03:04.240 --> 03:08.360
The man puts the ticket in his pocket quickly.

03:08.360 --> 03:11.080
The man gets into the taxi.

03:11.080 --> 03:14.320
The ticket falls out of his pocket.

03:14.320 --> 03:19.040
The wind blows the ticket into the air.

03:19.040 --> 03:21.320
Charlie catches the ticket.

03:21.320 --> 03:25.520
He has the ticket in his hand.

03:25.520 --> 03:27.680
Charlie waves his arms.

03:27.680 --> 03:29.480
He shouts out loudly.

03:29.480 --> 03:31.320
Your ticket.

03:31.320 --> 03:33.520
Your ticket.

03:33.520 --> 03:36.200
The man does not hear Charlie.

03:36.200 --> 03:39.360
The taxi moves away.

03:39.360 --> 03:41.880
Charlie stands on the pavement.

03:41.880 --> 03:50.280
The ticket is in his hand.

03:50.280 --> 03:53.800
Cafe Colombo closes at midnight.

03:53.800 --> 03:57.240
Charlie's home is far away.

03:57.240 --> 04:03.240
Every night, Charlie has a long walk home.

04:03.240 --> 04:05.800
Charlie's mother is waiting for him.

04:05.800 --> 04:09.320
He gives her all the money.

04:09.320 --> 04:12.440
Charlie has no father.

04:12.440 --> 04:16.840
Charlie has younger brothers and younger sisters.

04:16.840 --> 04:20.400
Charlie's mother needs the money.

04:20.400 --> 04:24.520
She buys food with the money.

04:24.520 --> 04:28.000
Charlie shows his mother the lottery ticket.

04:28.000 --> 04:31.280
His mother looks at the ticket.

04:31.280 --> 04:49.920
She reads the number 7, 5, 3, 8, 1, 2, 9, 4, 6.

04:49.920 --> 04:53.200
Is this the winning number?

04:53.200 --> 04:55.720
Perhaps it is.

04:55.720 --> 04:59.840
Saturday the 21st is tomorrow.

04:59.840 --> 05:08.600
Perhaps tomorrow will be their lucky day.

05:08.600 --> 05:11.040
Charlie is tired.

05:11.040 --> 05:14.440
He puts the ticket on his box.

05:14.440 --> 05:18.120
He falls asleep.

05:18.120 --> 05:22.800
Charlie has a dream.

05:22.800 --> 05:26.640
A goat comes into the house.

05:26.640 --> 05:30.160
The goat finds the ticket.

05:30.160 --> 05:34.400
The goat is eating the ticket.

05:34.400 --> 05:39.000
The goat eats the number 6.

05:39.000 --> 05:42.960
The goat eats the number 4.

05:42.960 --> 05:49.000
The goat eats the number 9.

05:49.000 --> 05:51.320
Charlie wakes up.

05:51.320 --> 05:53.480
It is morning.

05:53.480 --> 05:56.960
The ticket is not on the box.

05:56.960 --> 06:00.680
Where is the ticket?

06:00.680 --> 06:04.240
Charlie runs to the lottery office.

06:04.240 --> 06:07.040
Charlie sees his mother.

06:07.040 --> 06:11.400
She has the ticket.

06:11.400 --> 06:15.640
A man is shouting out the winning number.

06:15.640 --> 06:29.160
7, 5, 3, 8, 1, 2, 9, 4.

06:29.160 --> 06:33.480
Will the next number be 6?

06:33.480 --> 06:37.360
Will it be their lucky number?

06:37.360 --> 06:40.640
Will it be their lucky day?

